{"word":"βαπτός","slug":"βαπτός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>βαπτός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <a href='S:βάπτω'><el>βάπτω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>dipped, dyed, bright-coloured</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>for dyeing</i>, <el>χρώματα</el> <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>of water, <i>drawn by dipping vessels</i> (<a href='S:confer, compare'>cf.</a> <el>βάπτω</el> I. 3), <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}